Four children were rescued from their Philadelphia home Sunday after police say their mother locked them in the basement for 15 hours without food as punishment for bad behavior .
The woman , a single mother who reportedly works at the Philadelphia International Airport is now facing four counts of endangering the welfare of a child .
First responders rescued the woman 's three daughters and a son , ages 9 to 13 , at around 1.30 pm .
All four children were taken to be in good condition .